<p>In conclusion, understanding learning is a multifaceted journey, shaped by both historical philosophical insights and modern research methods. By utilizing different research paradigms and assessment methods, we gain a deeper understanding of the learning process, helping to refine educational practices and ultimately enhance how we teach and learn.</p>



